1. Create a folder on your computer for the project:

   Windows:  Create folder at  C:\panthera-ai\
   Mac/Linux: mkdir ~/panthera-ai

2. Place ALL your PANTHERA files into that folder:
   - All .jsx files (Phase1, Phase2, Phase3, Phase4)
   - All .py files (main.py, phase2.py, phase3.py, phase4.py)
   - All .sol files (PantheraRoyalty.sol, PantherToken.sol)
   - db/schema.sql
   - docker-compose.yml
   - deploy.sh
   - nginx/ folder
   - The GitHub files from this package (README.md, LICENSE, etc.)

3. COPY these new GitHub files into your folder:
   - README.md
   - LICENSE
   - .gitignore
   - SECURITY.md
   - .github/workflows/deploy.yml  (create the .github/workflows/ subfolder)

4. Open Git Bash / Terminal in your panthera-ai folder:

   Windows: Right-click inside the folder → "Git Bash Here"
   Mac/Linux: cd ~/panthera-ai

5. Run these commands ONE BY ONE:

   # Initialise git
   git init

   # Tell git about your GitHub repo
   git remote add origin https://github.com/peterudevi/panthera-ai.git

   # Stage all files (the .gitignore will automatically exclude secrets)
   git add .

   # Create your first commit
   git commit -m "feat: PANTHERA-AI Phase 1-4 — World's First AI Bot Marketplace

   Creator: Peter Chukwudi Udevi
   Platform: PANTHERA-AI
   Royalty: 5% gross revenue — Opay 8135140034 — Blockchain encoded
   Phases: 1 (foundation), 2 (marketplace), 3 (ML/automation), 4 (global dominance)

   Co-authored-by: Peter Chukwudi Udevi <Sizaperry@gmail.com>"

   # Push to GitHub
   git branch -M main
   git push -u origin main

6. GitHub will ask for your username + password.
   For password: use a Personal Access Token (NOT your GitHub password)

   Create token:
     GitHub → Settings → Developer Settings → Personal Access Tokens
     → Tokens (classic) → Generate new token
     → Name: panthera-deploy
     → Expiration: 1 year
     → Scopes: ✅ repo  ✅ workflow
     → Generate → COPY the token (shown only once)

   Use token as your "password" when git push asks

7. Visit https://github.com/peterudevi/panthera-ai
   You should see all your files and the README

