STEP 6 — SET UP AUTO-DEPLOY (GitHub → Your Server)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

This makes it so every time you push code to GitHub,
it automatically deploys to your live server.

A) Create SSH key for GitHub to use:

   On your SERVER (SSH in first):

   ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "github-actions-panthera" -f ~/.ssh/github_deploy
   # Press Enter twice (no passphrase)

   # Show the PUBLIC key (copy this)
   cat ~/.ssh/github_deploy.pub

   # Add to authorized keys on server
   cat ~/.ssh/github_deploy.pub >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

   # Show the PRIVATE key (copy this for GitHub)
   cat ~/.ssh/github_deploy

B) Add secrets to GitHub:

   Go to: https://github.com/peterudevi/panthera-ai
   → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret

   Add these 3 secrets:
   ┌─────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │ Name                │ Value                                  │
   ├─────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤
   │ SERVER_HOST         │ Your server IP (e.g. 165.22.84.123)   │
   │ SERVER_USER         │ root                                   │
   │ SERVER_SSH_KEY      │ (paste the PRIVATE key from above)    │
   └─────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┘

C) On your server, clone the repo:

   cd /root
   git clone https://github.com/peterudevi/panthera-ai.git
   cd panthera-ai
   cp .env.example .env
   nano .env   ← fill in your real values

D) Test auto-deploy:
   Make any small change to a file on your computer
   git add . && git commit -m "test: trigger deploy"
   git push

   Watch it deploy: GitHub → Actions tab
   Green checkmark = deployed successfully ✅

